values.name: ocaml-indent
values.description:
Simple OCaml source code indenter.

- Lexer based. Simple, easy to maintain, robust against P4 extensions
- Currently it just simply indent OCaml source code. ./indent foo.ml
- CLI interface. Editors should communicate with it. Not yet done at all.
- Just fixes indentations. No other code beautifier included.

The indentation tries to follow my style as possible. Neither the official one (does it exists?) or something already available (i.e. ocaml-mode/tuareg).

Lots more of testing required.

values.description: If you have used Python before, you for sure have used "range" in controlling loop's range and termination conditions. A great way to write simple for loops in an expressive way.
